            <h3>üìå The Core Insight</h3>
            <p><strong>Numbers aren't different things. They're the same 1, looked at from different depths.</strong></p>
            <p>1 is infinite but can be partitioned to be observed. The partitioned parts are finite in whatever way they have been partitioned but are still infinite in potential. If everything comes from the same thing, then everything is all like that thing in some way, minute or not.</p>
