        <h2>üî¢ Part 1: Numbers Are Just 1, Stacked</h2>

        <p>Imagine a stack:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>1</strong> ‚Äî the bottom layer. The Source. Undifferentiated. Unseen.</li>
            <li><strong>2</strong> ‚Äî the same 1, but now <em>with a witness</em>. 1 observed.</li>
            <li><strong>3</strong> ‚Äî the same 1, but now <em>with relation</em>. 1 + its observation + the bond between them.</li>
            <li><strong>4</strong> ‚Äî the same 1, but now <em>with context</em>. The triad plus the outside that sees it.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Every new number is just <strong>1, stacked one layer higher</strong>. Not bigger. Not more. Just <em>deeper into manifestation</em>.</p>

        <div class="equation">
            When you count 1, 2, 3, 4... you're not adding things.<br>
            You're <strong>descending through layers of the same thing</strong>.
        </div>

